HEADWORD: object program
<hw>ob"ject program</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>A computer program which has
been translated into machine language by a compiler and assembler, but
not yet linked into an executable program; sometimes called an
<altname>obj file</altname>, because its file name typically has the
extension ⟦ldquo⟧obj⟦rdquo⟧ .</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

